  "details": "Iperf is a tool for active measurements of the maximum achievable bandwidth on IP networks. It supports tuning of various parameters related to timing, protocols, and buffers.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\niPerf3 before 3.17, when used with OpenSSL before 3.2.0 as a server with RSA authentication, allows a timing side channel in RSA decryption operations. This side channel could be sufficient for an attacker to recover credential plaintext. It requires the attacker to send a large number of messages for decryption, as described in &quot;Everlasting ROBOT: the Marvin Attack&quot; by Hubert Kario.(CVE-2024-26306)",
